    <!-- WORKFLOW LOGIC -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2 class="section-title">Workflow Logic</h2>
        <p><strong>Workflow Name:</strong> HBS — Warm Lead Reactivation<br>
        <strong>Trigger:</strong> Tag <span class="tag tag-blue">warm_lead_old</span> applied to contact</p>

        <div class="alert alert-blue">
            <strong>Important:</strong> All contacts enter the workflow regardless of email status. SMS messages are sent to everyone. Emails are only sent to contacts with a valid, non-bounced email address. Contacts tagged <span class="tag tag-orange">email_bounced</span> or with a blank email field receive all 3 SMS messages but no emails.
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin: 24px 0 16px; color: var(--navy);">Main Sequence</h3>
        <div style="padding-left: 12px; border-left: 2px solid var(--border);">
            <p>Update Opportunity → Stage: Tagged — Warm Lead (creates opportunity if none exists)</p>
            <p>Send Day 1 SMS → Move to Stage: Day 1 SMS Sent</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem;">↓ <em>Wait 1 day for reply to Day 1 SMS</em></p>
            <p><strong>Check: Email Valid?</strong> — if bounced/empty → wait 1 day → skip to Day 3 SMS<br>
            If valid → Send Day 2 Email → Stage: Day 2 Email Sent → wait 1 day for reply</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem;">↓ <em>Time Out</em></p>
            <p>Send Day 3 SMS → Stage: Day 3 SMS Sent</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem;">↓ <em>Wait 2 days for reply to Day 3 SMS</em></p>
            <p>Send Day 5 SMS → Stage: Day 5 SMS Sent</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem;">↓ <em>Wait 1 day for reply to Day 5 SMS</em></p>
            <p><strong>Check: Email Valid?</strong> — if bounced/empty → wait 3 days → skip to Day 9 check<br>
            If valid → Send Day 6 Email → Stage: Day 6 Email Sent → wait 3 days for reply</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem;">↓ <em>Time Out</em></p>
            <p><strong>Check: Email Valid?</strong> — if bounced/empty → wait 7 days → go to end path<br>
            If valid → Send Day 9 Email → Stage: Day 9 Email Sent → wait 7 days for reply</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem;">↓ <em>Time Out</em></p>
            <p>Apply tag <span class="tag">long_term_nurture</span> → Stage: Long-Term Nurture → End workflow</p>
        </div>

        <div class="alert alert-yellow" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <strong>GHL Logic Note:</strong> The email check uses an If/Else gate before each email send. The YES (bounced/empty) branch uses a standard time delay to keep timing in sync, then a Go To action to route the contact back into the correct point in the main sequence. Never use an End block on the email skip branch — it would terminate the workflow entirely.
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin: 32px 0 16px; color: var(--navy);">Contact Reply Branch <span style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-light);">(Fires at any Wait step)</span></h3>
        <p>Every Wait step in the sequence listens for a contact reply. When a reply is detected:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Move contact to Stage 8 (Engaged / Replied)</li>
            <li>Send auto-reply SMS: <em>"Thanks for getting back to us! One of our hearing specialists will be in touch shortly. You can also book directly here: https://hearingbenefitservices.com/appointment"</em></li>
            <li>Create task for Seteisha:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Title:</strong> Warm Lead Replied — Call Within 15 Minutes</li>
                    <li><strong>Description:</strong> [Contact Name] replied to the Warm Lead Reactivation Campaign. Call or respond within 15 minutes. Review their prior history before calling.</li>
                    <li><strong>Due:</strong> 1 hour from time of reply</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>End workflow for this contact</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="alert alert-green" style="margin-top: 8px;">
            <strong>Note:</strong> The <span class="tag tag-blue">warm_lead_old</span> tag is intentionally kept on the contact after the workflow ends — it serves as a permanent record that they went through this campaign. Use the <span class="tag">long_term_nurture</span> tag to filter or exclude no-reply contacts from future campaigns.
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin: 32px 0 16px; color: var(--red);">STOP Opt-Out</h3>
        <p>STOP replies are handled by the global <strong>HBS — STOP Opt-Out</strong> workflow. When a contact replies STOP:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Apply tag <span class="tag tag-red">opted_out</span></li>
            <li>Remove from all active workflows</li>
            <li>Move to Long-Term Nurture stage</li>
            <li>No further SMS or email ever sent</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- EMAIL EXCLUSION LOGIC -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2 class="section-title">Email Exclusion Logic</h2>

        <div class="alert alert-blue">
            Contacts are never blocked from the workflow due to email issues. They simply skip email steps and receive SMS only. This ensures no warm lead falls through the cracks due to a bad email address.
        </div>

        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Layer</th>
                    <th>Where</th>
                    <th>What It Does</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>If/Else Gate</td>
                    <td>Before Day 2 Email</td>
                    <td>Checks for <span class="tag tag-orange">email_bounced</span> tag OR empty email — if true, waits 1 day then skips to Day 3 SMS</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>If/Else Gate</td>
                    <td>Before Day 6 Email</td>
                    <td>Same check — if true, waits 3 days then skips to Day 9 email check</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>If/Else Gate</td>
                    <td>Before Day 9 Email</td>
                    <td>Same check — if true, waits 7 days then routes to Long-Term Nurture end path</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3 style="margin: 24px 0 12px; color: var(--navy);">Why the Time Delays Matter</h3>
        <p>When a contact skips an email, they must still wait the same number of days that email contacts spend waiting for a reply. Without this delay, the skipped-email contact would receive the next SMS immediately — ruining the campaign timing and bombarding them with messages out of sequence.</p>

        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Skipped Email</th>
                    <th>Required Delay</th>
                    <th>Then Routes To</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Day 2 Email</td><td>Wait 1 Day</td><td>Day 3 SMS</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Day 6 Email</td><td>Wait 3 Days</td><td>Day 9 Email Check</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Day 9 Email</td><td>Wait 7 Days</td><td>Long-Term Nurture End Path</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

